# Trivy CVE suppressions for transitive dependencies that cannot be upgraded
# without breaking SDK functionality.
#
# Each section documents WHY the CVE cannot be fixed and what the actual
# exposure risk is in production.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# axios@0.21.4 and @0.25.0
# Source: @cosmjs/tendermint-rpc@0.30.1 and @docknetwork/wallet-sdk-wasm@1.7.6
# Risk:   The axios 0.x → 1.x upgrade has breaking API changes that would break
#         CosmJS and the Dock wallet SDK. The SSRF/proxy CVEs are unexploitable
#         because the wallet server only connects to known cheqd RPC endpoints
#         (never relays user-supplied URLs to axios).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2025-27152
CVE-2026-25639
CVE-2026-42033
CVE-2026-42035
CVE-2026-42043
CVE-2026-44486
CVE-2026-44487
CVE-2026-44492
CVE-2026-44495
CVE-2026-44496

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# protobufjs@6.11.x
# Source: cosmjs-types@0.7.2 via @cheqd/sdk@5.4.3 → @cosmjs/proto-signing,
#         @cosmjs/stargate, @confio/ics23
# Risk:   cosmjs-types@0.7.2 uses the protobufjs@^6 API. Forcing 7.x+ breaks
#         the CosmJS blockchain interaction layer. The code-execution vector
#         (CVE-2026-41242) requires feeding a malicious protobuf definition at
#         load time — the wallet server only loads protobuf schemas bundled with
#         the SDK package, not user-supplied schemas.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-41242
CVE-2026-44289
CVE-2026-44290
CVE-2026-44291
CVE-2026-44293

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# tar@6.2.1
# Source: node-gyp@8.4.1 inside sqlite3@5.1.7
# Risk:   node-gyp@8.x requires tar@^6. This tar instance is only used at
#         build time to download sqlite3 native prebuilds — never to extract
#         user-supplied archives at runtime. Path-traversal CVEs require
#         extracting a malicious tarball, which doesn't happen in production.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# undici@5.29.0
# Source: @digitalbazaar/http-client@3.4.1 inside jsonld@6.0.0
# Risk:   @digitalbazaar/http-client@3.4.1 requires undici@^5. The 5.x → 6.x
#         upgrade has breaking API changes. The DoS vectors (CVE-2026-1526,
#         CVE-2026-2229) require sending malformed HTTP responses from a server
#         the wallet connects to — mitigated by connecting only to known
#         trusted DID registries (cheqd, PolygonID). WebSocket path is unused.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-1526
CVE-2026-2229

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# underscore@1.13.6 / @1.13.4
# Source: jsonpath@1.3.0 (pins to exact 1.13.6); protobufjs@6.x CLI tools
# Risk:   npm overrides cannot force jsonpath's exact-version pin or update
#         protobufjs's bundled CLI node_modules. The DoS vector
#         (CVE-2026-27601) requires evaluating a crafted jsonpath expression
#         from untrusted input. In the wallet server, jsonpath is used by
#         @sphereon/pex only when processing presentation definitions — input
#         that comes from verified VC presentation templates, not end users.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-27601

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# protobufjs@6.11.x (additional CVEs) and ws@7.5.10
# Source: @cosmjs/stargate-cjs and @cosmjs/tendermint-rpc-cjs (CosmJS 0.30.x
#         CJS compat layer bundled inside @cheqd/sdk → @docknetwork/cheqd-blockchain-api)
# Risk:   Same bundled-tarball situation as the axios/protobufjs CVEs above —
#         npm overrides cannot reach nested node_modules inside published CJS
#         packages. The ws DoS (CVE-2026-48779) requires a malicious server
#         sending tiny fragments; the wallet only connects to known cheqd RPC
#         WebSocket endpoints. The protobufjs DoS requires a malicious .proto
#         message; the wallet only processes SDK-bundled schemas.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-48712
CVE-2026-48779

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# fast-uri@3.1.2
# Source: ajv@8.18.0 → @modelcontextprotocol/sdk (both api and wallet servers)
# Risk:   ajv@8 requires fast-uri@^3.x; 4.x is a breaking API change that
#         ajv does not support. The CVEs are parsing edge-cases in URI
#         validation that are not reachable via MCP tool input schemas.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-6321
CVE-2026-6322

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# tmp@0.2.x
# Source: protobufjs/cli nested inside cosmjs-types-cjs, @cosmjs/stargate-cjs,
#         @cosmjs/proto-signing-cjs, @confio/ics23 (CosmJS CJS compat bundles)
# Risk:   tmp is a CLI build tool for protobuf code generation; it is never
#         invoked at runtime. npm overrides cannot reach nested node_modules
#         inside published CJS bundle packages. No user-controlled paths are
#         passed to tmp in production.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2026-44705
